Interface OnMapReadyCallback

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnimatedImageSourceActivity, BasicLocationPulsingCircleActivity, BottomSheetActivity.BottomSheetFragment, BottomSheetActivity.MainMapFragment, CameraAnimationTypeActivity, CameraAnimatorActivity, CameraPositionActivity, CustomizedLocationPulsingCircleActivity, DebugModeActivity, DeviceIndependentTestActivity, DynamicInfoWindowAdapterActivity, GradientLineActivity, GridSourceActivity, ImageInLabelActivity, InfoWindowActivity, LatLngBoundsForCameraActivity, LocationComponentActivationActivity, LocationMapChangeActivity, LocationModesActivity, ManualLocationUpdatesActivity, MapFragment, MapFragmentActivity, MaxMinZoomActivity, PolygonActivity, RealTimeGeoJsonActivity, ScrollByActivity, StretchableImageActivity, SupportMapFragment, SupportMapFragmentActivity, SymbolGeneratorActivity, SymbolLayerActivity, TextureViewDebugModeActivity

    public interface OnMapReadyCallback
    Interface definition for a callback to be invoked when the map is ready to be used.

    Once an instance of this interface is set on a MapFragment or MapView object, the onMapReady(MapboxMap) method is triggered when the map is ready to be used and provides an instance of MapboxMap.
